en_683493_0	The open dialogue where all candidates of the Presidential Election 2019 is expected to present their policies to the public on one platform commenced today.
en_683493_1	The event named ‘Public Platform’ was held at the Sugathadasa Indoor Stadium in Colombo.
en_683493_2	Taking part in the programme UNF presidential candidate said that projects productive to the country and the people should be implemented by understanding universal economic fluctuations.
en_683493_3	The foreign investments received by the country should be handled properly.
en_683493_4	He said that persons with knowledge about the subjects should be used to minimize the debt burden.
en_683493_5	The production capacity should be increased and part of the revenue received through such activities should be utilized to pay the loans to create a country without a debt burden.
en_683493_6	He said that steps should be taken to ensure national security and supremacy of the law.
en_683493_7	The organisations that implement such measures should be depoliticised.
en_683493_8	Speaking further he said that opportunity should not be given to get political benefits by creating disputes among communities and followers of various religions.
en_683493_9	National security of the country should be protected while providing rights of all communities in a unitary country.
en_683493_10	Steps should be taken based on the policies for the betterment of the future generations.
en_683493_11	Speaking at the programme National People’s Power Alliance Presidential Candidate Anura Kumara Dissanayake said that a structure will be created where all communities will get their rights.
en_683493_12	Children should be taught the liberation mentioned in all religions.
en_683493_13	He said that future Sri Lanka needs a human being who values equality.
en_683493_14	The country should be built based on education, health and sports.
en_683493_15	The event is a collaborative effort of the AFRIEL Youth Network and the March 12 Movement of the PAFFREL Organization.
